            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve"><head>Text</head><ab><lb n="1"/>
                <supplied reason="lost"><gap reason="lost" quantity="1" unit="character"/></supplied> Hora<supplied reason="lost" cert="low">tius - f(ilius)</supplied> <lb n="2"/>Balb<supplied reason="lost">us<certainty locus="name" match="preceding-sibling::text()" cert="low"/> <gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></supplied> <lb n="3"/>municipibus <supplied reason="lost">su</supplied><lb break="no" n="4"/>eis incoleisque <supplied reason="lost">lo</supplied><lb break="no" n="5"/>ca sepultura<supplied reason="lost">e</supplied> <expan><abbr>s</abbr><ex>ua</ex></expan> <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>ecunia</ex></expan> dat <lb n="6"/>extra au<supplied reason="lost">ct</supplied>orateis et <lb n="7"/>quei sibei <supplied reason="lost">la</supplied>queo <expan><abbr>manu</abbr><ex>m</ex></expan> <lb n="8"/>attulissent et quei <lb n="9"/>quaestum spurcum <lb n="10"/>professi essent singuleis <lb n="11"/>in fronte <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>edes</ex></expan> X in agrum <expan><abbr>p</abbr><ex>edes</ex></expan> X <lb n="12"/>inter pontem Sapis et titu<lb break="no" n="13"/>lum superiorem qui est in <lb n="14"/>fine fundi Fangoniani <lb n="15"/>in quibus loceis nemo huma<lb break="no" n="16"/>tus erit qui volet sibei <lb n="17"/>vivous monumentum fa<lb break="no" n="18"/>ciet in quibus loceis hu<lb break="no" n="19"/>mati erunt ei d<expan><ex>um</ex><abbr>t</abbr><ex>axat</ex></expan> quei <lb n="20"/>humatus erit postereis<lb break="no" n="21"/>que eius monumentum <lb n="22"/>fieri licebit
            </ab></div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Ursprung des fundus Fangonianus: Susini bringt ihn mit C. Fuficius Fango in Verbindung, einem centurio, der unter Caesar Senator wurde (CIL X 3578 aus Acerrae). Herkunft der Fuficii Fangones: Campania. (A): Tafel. (B): Z. 1: Horat[tius].</p>
            </div>
